==觀點==
===戀童與兒童性虐待===
坎托在接受[[有线电视新闻网|美國有线电视新闻网]]訪問時稱，社會應為認為兒童擁有性吸引力但沒有犯過性罪行的人提供一定支持，以使之在保持零犯罪記錄的情況下，活得更美好。在他看來，值得社会制裁的並不是有關想法（戀童），而是行為（性騷擾兒童）：「人們並不能夠選擇戀童與否，但能夠選擇不去性騷擾兒童」<ref>{{cite web |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2012/06/21/opinion/cantor-pedophila-sandusky/index.html |author=Cantor, James |title=Do pedophiles deserve sympathy? |publisher=[[有线电视新闻网|CNN]] |date=2012-06-21 |accessdate=2012-09-24 |archive-date=2019-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190804034436/https://edition.cnn.com/2012/06/21/opinion/cantor-pedophila-sandusky/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

坎托表示，根據他的經驗，對兒童出手的戀童者「多在感到最絕望的時候才下手——亦即他們認為沒什麼可失去，沒什麼值得保護的時候」。他建議治療師應採用[[认知行为疗法|认知行为疗法]]等手段，使其絕望感或疏離感得以減少，最終使戀童者過上「沒有犯罪的豐富人生」<ref>{{cite book |author=Cantor, J. M. |editor1=Binik, Yitzchak M. |editor2=Hall, Kathryn S. K. |year=2014 |chapter="Gold-star" Pedophiles in General Sex Therapy Practice |title=Principles and Practice of Sex Therapy, Fifth Edition |pages=222–223}}</ref>。

坎托在接受訪問時說道：「我們看不到使人不再戀童的可能性……唯一合乎逻辑的方案就是幫助這些人盡可能地過上健康豐彩的人生。對於一些人而言，他們的生活基礎就是一份穩定的工作、一處安身之所、對於人身安全的保障……当我们让其找不到工作或住處時，那麼他們就不能安身立命」<ref name="theglobeandmail.com">{{cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/life/health-and-fitness/health/the-most-viscerally-hated-group-on-earth-documentary-explores-how-intervention-can-stop-pedophiles/article29072878/|title='The most viscerally hated group on earth': Documentary explores how intervention can stop pedophiles|publisher=|via=The Globe and Mail|accessdate=2020-11-07|archive-date=2016-08-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816231057/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/life/health-and-fitness/health/the-most-viscerally-hated-group-on-earth-documentary-explores-how-intervention-can-stop-pedophiles/article29072878/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

坎托認為線上組織Virtuous Pedophiles有助於防止人們對兒童從事性虐待行為。這個組織由對兒童擁有性興趣的人組成，不過他們整體上認為性侵犯兒童是一種錯誤的行為<ref name="Salon">{{cite news |last=Clarke-Flory |first=Tracy |title=Meet pedophiles who mean well: The men behind VirtuousPedophiles.com are attracted to children but devoted to denying their desires |newspaper=Salon.com |date=2012-07-01 |url=http://www.salon.com/2012/07/01/meet_pedophiles_who_mean_well/ |accessdate=2020-11-07 |archive-date=2021-03-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210302174713/https://www.salon.com/2012/07/01/meet_pedophiles_who_mean_well/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。他稱，這個網站會向害怕污名化而不敢尋求傳統手段協助的人提供支持，並向警方報案<ref>{{cite web |title=Four Misconceptions About Pedophiles |url=http://www.cbc.ca/firsthand/features/four-misconceptions-about-pedophiles |website=CBC |accessdate=2018-06-18 |language=en |date=2016-03-10 |archive-date=2021-02-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210220175631/https://www.cbc.ca/firsthand/features/four-misconceptions-about-pedophiles |dead-url=no }}</ref>。他说戀童者的「慾望、感情跟一般人一樣強烈。这是一种不能跟人訴說、深不見底的長痛」<ref name="walrus">{{cite web |last1=Lewsen |first1=Simon |title=Why Would Someone Choose to Be a Monster? |url=https://thewalrus.ca/why-would-someone-choose-to-be-a-monster/ |website=The Walrus |accessdate=2018-06-18 |language=en-CA |date=2016-09-28 |archive-date=2019-02-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190223020015/https://thewalrus.ca/why-would-someone-choose-to-be-a-monster/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

坎托反對[[社會對同性戀的態度|同性戀跟戀童有關]]的說法，他指出：「在科学文献中，有相当坚实的证据表明，同性恋和恋童之间绝对没有任何關係」<ref name="whiteman">{{cite web |url=http://articles.cnn.com/2010-04-14/world/vatican.homosexuality.pedophilia_1_pedophilia-gay-rights-cardinal-tarcisio-bertone?_s=PM:WORLD |title=Gay outrage over cardinal's child abuse comment |publisher=[[有线电视新闻网|CNN]] |first=Hilary |last=Whiteman |date=2010-04-14 |accessdate=2010-09-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101018182049/http://articles.cnn.com/2010-04-14/world/vatican.homosexuality.pedophilia_1_pedophilia-gay-rights-cardinal-tarcisio-bertone?_s=PM%3AWORLD |archivedate=2010-10-18 }}</ref>。他反对禁止已出櫃的同性戀者參與童军的做法：「若說歷史教會了我們什麼的話，那就是使人隱瞞和感到羞恥的環境會為虐待事件加添一澆油」<ref>{{cite news
